-- Armstrong Interview With Winfrey Viewed by More Than 28 Million
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-01-23T05:00:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-23/armstrong-interview-with-winfrey-viewed-by-more-than-28-million.html
Lance Armstrong’s interview with
 Oprah Winfrey  in which he said he cheated to win seven Tour de
France titles was seen by more than 28 million viewers over the
two-day broadcast, Discovery Communications Inc. said.  More than 12 million tuned into Winfrey’s OWN channel in
the U.S. and another 15 million watched on international
stations, with 800,000 streaming it live online, Discovery said,
citing Nielsen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  